Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄4-inch-thick rounds (no need to peel). Peel and
thinly slice @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim
and remove strings from @sugar snap peas{4%ounce}. Trim @scallions{2}, then cut
crosswise into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In the last ~{5%minutes} of cooking, remove sheet from oven and carefully add
garlic; return to top rack until potatoes are golden brown.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over high heat. Add green
beans, snap peas, and scallions; cook, stirring continuously, until charred
and tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in lemon zest and season generously with salt and pepper.
Transfer veggies to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with half the
@brown sugar bourbon seasoning{10.8%g}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> You'll use the rest of the seasoning later.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add salmon,
skin sides down, and cook until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through,
~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate.

While salmon cooks, heat a medium, dry pan over medium heat. Add
@pecans{1%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant,
~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer pecans to a #small bowl{}.

Add @maple syrup{2%tablespoon}, @miso sauce concentrate{1%unit},
half the @brown sugar{1%tablespoon}, remaining brown sugar bourbon seasoning,
1⁄4 cup water, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4) to pan used
for pecans. Return pan to medium-high heat. Add toasted pecans; cook, stirring
occasionally, until sauce begins to thicken, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt to taste.

Toss veggies with a big squeeze of lemon juice.

Divide salmon, veggies, and garlic potatoes between plates. Spoon glaze over
salmon. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.